Substitute each $x$ into $y=\dfrac{4}{3}x-12$:<ul><li>A) $(0,	frac{4}{3})$: $\dfrac{4}{3}(0)-12=-12 
e \dfrac{4}{3}$ &mdash; eliminate.</li><li>B) $(1,6)$: $\dfrac{4}{3}(1)-12=\dfrac{4}{3}-\dfrac{36}{3}=-\dfrac{32}{3} 
e 6$ &mdash; eliminate.</li><li>C) $(12,4)$: $\dfrac{4}{3}(12)-12=16-12=4$ &mdash; matches.</li><li>D) $(14,2)$: $\dfrac{4}{3}(14)-12=\dfrac{56}{3}-\dfrac{36}{3}=\dfrac{20}{3} 
e 2$ &mdash; eliminate.</li></ul><strong>C</strong> is correct.
